content:
The General Liability line of business gives you a fully functional example of the Essential Business product model, rating procedure, and business processes for quoting.

You can use this application for reference or as a base to develop your own product models and business processes.

Product Model: Essential Business
Rating Procedure: Rating_EssentialBusiness

The product model provides the structure for the data JSON that moves through the business processes. The Essential Business product model is single-instance, which means that we intend customers to insure only one business per policy. All coverages have been designed to be configured at the policy level.

The rating procedures take information from the prospective customer during quoting business processes and calculate prices for coverages. The product model rating simulation rolls up those prices and calculates the total premium.

Commercial Quote Business Process

This process guides prospective customers (and agents and brokers helping those prospects) to get a rated quote for a commercial product:

1. Use the Essential Business Product Model
2. Apply the Rating_EssentialBusiness procedure
3. Calculate the prices for coverages
4. Roll up the prices using the product model rating simulation

When we quote and endorse Commercial products, our pricing services use the product model data, product rating procedure, and pricing formulas to price the coverages.

The Commercial Quote Business Process is a fully functional example of the Essential Business product model, rating procedure, and business processes for quoting.
title: Essential Business Insurance Overview
